return ['messages'=>['<p>Proyecto</p>'=>'<p>Project</p>','<p>Si miramos a nuestro alrededor, podremos darnos cuenta de la enorme desinformación de la que estamos rodeados, en muchas temáticas, una de ellas, la sexualidad, y más específicamente, nuestra zona genital.</p><p>-</p><p>¿Acaso no todos tenemos genitales?</p><p>¿Acaso no son todos de diferentes formas y colores, pero igual de válidos y hermosos?</p><p>La respuesta es sí, pero pareciera que se nos olvida.</p><p>-</p><p>Es con esta finalidad que he visto necesario crear este proyecto, que no busca crear morbo, sino normalizar el hecho de que todos tenemos genitales, y que no importa cómo se vean, son bellos.</p><p>Ojalá con estas imágenes puedas verte reflejadx a ti, entre toda esta variedad.</p><p>Ojalá recuerdes, después de ver este proyecto, que todos los genitales son merecedores de amor, pero no por eso tienen que ser sexualizados.</p><p>Ojalá te cuestiones ciertas ideas que quizá tengas arraigadas.</p><p>Ojalá reconozcas que detrás de estas fotografías, hay personas.</p>'=>'<p>If we look around us, we can realize the enormous misinformation we are surrounded by on many subjects, one of them, sexuality, and more specifically, our genitalia.</p><p>-</p><p>Don\'t we all have genitals?</p><p>Aren\'t they all different shapes and colors, but equally valid and beautiful?</p><p>The answer is yes, but we seem to forget it.</p><p>-</p><p>It is with this in mind that I have found it necessary to create this project, which does not seek to create morbidity, but to normalize the fact that we all have genitals, and that no matter how they look, they are beautiful.</p><p>Hopefully with these images you can see yourself reflected in all this variety.</p><p>Hopefully you will remember, after watching this project, that all genitalia are worthy of love, but that does not mean they have to be sexualized.</p><p>I hope you will question certain ideas that may be ingrained in your mind.</p><p>I hope you recognize that behind these photographs, there are people.</p>','<p>Si quieres participar en este proyecto, es necesario que te encuentres en Barcelona. Si es así, puedes contactarme para coordinar:</p>'=>'<p>If you enjoyed the above content, feel free to share it with anyone you think might also like it. If you want to collaborate in an even more generous way, I leave you a button where you can do it:</p>','All'=>'All','Donación'=>'Donation','Genitales Anónimos'=>'Anonymous Genitalia','New Gallery'=>'New Gallery','Separador'=>'Separator','editor-text-editor-103ef85f'=>'<p>If you enjoyed the above content, feel free to share it with anyone you think might also like it. If you want to collaborate in an even more generous way, I leave you a button where you can do it:</p>','editor-text-editor-7178ccf'=>'<p>If we look around us, we can realize the enormous misinformation we are surrounded by on many subjects, one of them, sexuality, and more specifically, our genitalia.</p><p>-</p><p>Don\'t we all have genitals?</p><p>Aren\'t they all different shapes and colors, but equally valid and beautiful?</p><p>The answer is yes, but we seem to forget it.</p><p>-</p><p>It is with this in mind that I have found it necessary to create this project, which does not seek to create morbidity, but to normalize the fact that we all have genitals, and that no matter how they look, they are beautiful.</p><p>Hopefully with these images you can see yourself reflected in all this variety.</p><p>Hopefully you will remember, after watching this project, that all genitalia are worthy of love, but that does not mean they have to be sexualized.</p><p>I hope you will question certain ideas that may be ingrained in your mind.</p><p>I hope you recognize that behind these photographs, there are people.</p>','editor-text-editor-cef61eb'=>'<p>Project</p>','gallery-gallery_title-cc8ef8e-46ba3da'=>'New Gallery','show_all_galleries_label-gallery-cc8ef8e'=>'All','text-button-2c33426c'=>'Donation','text-divider-4120372'=>'Separator','text-divider-70fea4bf'=>'Separator','title-heading-baeb9ac'=>'Anonymous Genitalia']];
